comments.body:
I feel like this would be a lot simpler by just using the `time_added` field, instead of adding a parallel data structure? It would be an O(n) scan, but it's capped at `MAX_TRANSACTION`s.

```suggestion
        const CTransactionRef oldest{std::ranges::min_element(
            m_transactions, {},
            [](const auto& el) { return el.second.time_added; })};
```

